.SH NAME
\fBpynakotheka.py\fR \- pynakotheka is a simple python script which generates static HTML photo albums.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.BI "pynakotheka.py <options> [source_dir [target_dir]]"
.br
.br
.sp

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pynakotheka.py
is a simple python script which generates
static HTML photo albums to be added to web sites or to be burnt in CDs.

The gallery can contain folders and/or pictures
and the folders can contain other folders and/or pictures, recursively.
There are 4 views: folder, tree, thumbnails and photo detail (with or
without exif info). You can even create your own templates easily.

.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.B "source_dir"
Location of the source photos, defaults to current dir
.TP
.B "target_dir"
Directory where to save the gallery, defaults to current dir

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B "\-h, \-\-help"
Show this text
.TP
.B "\-q, \-\-quiet"
Don't show progress information messages, default SHOW
.TP
.B "\-c, \-\-color"
Show information messages with colors, default NO COLOR
.TP
.B "\-o, \-\-copy\-originals"
Copy original images to the gallery, default NO
.TP
.B "\-s, \-\-thumbsize"
Thumbnail size, defaults to 250
.TP
.B "\-i, \-\-imagesize"
Image size, defaults to 640
.TP
.B "\-d, \-\-templates\-dir"
Path to templates directory, defaults to "/usr/share/pynakotheka/templates"
.TP
.B "\-t, \-\-template"
Template to use, defaults to "default"
.TP
.B "\-\-clean=all|images|html"
Remove all files / images / html and style files generated by the program


